<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 5. Pollen stained with lactophenol cotton blue. a, b Spartina anglica, fertile pollen [Canada, British Columbia, Williams 2004 - 3 (CAN)] c Spartina xtownsendii, sterile pollen [England, Hampshire, 1877, Groves s. n. (CAN)] d Spartina xtownsendii, sterile pollen [Canada, British Columbia, Saarela & Percy 791 (CAN)]" , "Figure 4. Anthers of a Spartina anglica [U. S. A., Washington, Pacific Co., Zika 17595, WTU], bar = 3 mm. b Spartina xtownsendii [England, Hythe, Southampton, Marchant s. n., UBCV 221074], bar = 3 mm. Anthers of Spartina anglica are fully exserted at anthesis, dehiscent, and the pollen is fertile. The longitudinal splitting of the anthers is a good indicator of dehiscence. Anthers in Spartina xtownsendii are not or incompletely exserted at anthesis, indehiscent, and the pollen is sterile. Photos: J. M. Saarela." , "Figure 3. Photograph of a specimen of Spartina anglica collected in Boundary Bay, south of Vancouver, British Columbia (Williams 2004 - 2, UBC). Image published with the permission of the University of British Columbia Herbarium, Beaty Biodiversity Museum." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/10020" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/10019" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/10018" .

